str2: Fourteen. From deka and tessares; ten and four, i.e. Fourteen.
A year. Apparently a primary word; a year.
A primary preposition denoting the channel of an act; through.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: To go up, mount, ascend; of things: I rise, spring up, come up. From ana and the base of basis; to go up.
Probably from the same as pale; anew, i.e. back, once more, or furthermore or on the other hand.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
The Greek form of the Hebrew name: Jerusalem. Of Hebrew origin; Hierosolyma
(a) gen: with, in company with, (b) acc: (1) behind, beyond, after, of place, (2) after, of time, with nouns, neut. of adjectives.
Of Chaldee origin; son of Nabas; Barnabas, an Israelite.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To take along as a companion. From sun and paralambano; to take along in company.
Of Latin origin but uncertain significance; Titus, a Christian.
